{"paragraphs":[{"cues":[{"time":960,"text":"So it was the fall of 1902,"},{"time":3519,"text":"and President Theodore Roosevelt"},{"time":5437,"text":"needed a little break from the White House,"},{"time":7217,"text":"so he took a train to Mississippi"},{"time":9595,"text":"to do a little black bear hunting outside of a town"},{"time":11723,"text":"called Smedes."},{"time":13910,"text":"The first day of the hunt,\nthey didn't see a single bear,"},{"time":15970,"text":"so it was a big bummer for everyone,"},{"time":17490,"text":"but the second day, the dogs cornered one"},{"time":20334,"text":"after a really long chase, but by that point,"},{"time":22734,"text":"the president had given up"},{"time":24178,"text":"and gone back to camp for lunch,"},{"time":25920,"text":"so his hunting guide cracked the animal"},{"time":28531,"text":"on the top of the head with the butt of his rifle,"},{"time":31199,"text":"and then tied it up to a tree"},{"time":32907,"text":"and started tooting away on his bugle"},{"time":35519,"text":"to call Roosevelt back so he could have the honor"},{"time":37558,"text":"of shooting it."},{"time":39074,"text":"The bear was a female."},{"time":41431,"text":"It was dazed, injured,"},{"time":44007,"text":"severely underweight, a little mangy-looking,"},{"time":47654,"text":"and when Roosevelt saw this animal"},{"time":49721,"text":"tied up to the tree,"},{"time":51343,"text":"he just couldn't bring himself to fire at it."},{"time":53142,"text":"He felt like that would go against his code"},{"time":55293,"text":"as a sportsman."}]},{"cues":[{"time":57259,"text":"A few days later, the scene was memorialized"},{"time":59960,"text":"in a political cartoon back in Washington."},{"time":62995,"text":"It was called \"Drawing a Line in Mississippi,\""},{"time":65116,"text":"and it showed Roosevelt with\nhis gun down and his arm out,"},{"time":67495,"text":"sparing the bear's life,"},{"time":69132,"text":"and the bear was sitting on its hind legs"},{"time":70658,"text":"with these two big, frightened, wide eyes"},{"time":72696,"text":"and little ears pricked up at the top of its head."},{"time":74826,"text":"It looked really helpless, like you just wanted to"},{"time":76334,"text":"sweep it up into your arms"},{"time":78034,"text":"and reassure it."},{"time":79250,"text":"It wouldn't have looked familiar at the time,"},{"time":80716,"text":"but if you go looking for the cartoon now,"},{"time":82784,"text":"you recognize the animal right away:"},{"time":85520,"text":"It's a teddy bear."},{"time":87474,"text":"And this is how the teddy bear was born."},{"time":89095,"text":"Essentially, toymakers took\nthe bear from the cartoon,"},{"time":91603,"text":"turned it into a plush toy, and then named it"},{"time":93203,"text":"after President Roosevelt -- Teddy's bear."}]},{"cues":[{"time":96397,"text":"And I do feel a little ridiculous"},{"time":98541,"text":"that I'm up here on this stage"},{"time":101476,"text":"and I'm choosing to use my time"},{"time":102894,"text":"to tell you about a 100-year-old story"},{"time":105162,"text":"about the invention of a squishy kid's toy,"},{"time":108260,"text":"but I'd argue that the invention of the teddy bear,"},{"time":112220,"text":"inside that story is a more important story,"},{"time":115181,"text":"a story about how dramatically our ideas"},{"time":117409,"text":"about nature can change,"},{"time":119005,"text":"and also about how, on the planet right now,"},{"time":122345,"text":"the stories that we tell"},{"time":124441,"text":"are dramatically changing nature."}]},{"cues":[{"time":126709,"text":"Because think about the teddy bear."},{"time":128241,"text":"For us, in retrospect, it feels like an obvious fit,"},{"time":130746,"text":"because bears are so cute and cuddly,"},{"time":132249,"text":"and who wouldn't want to give\none to their kids to play with,"},{"time":134721,"text":"but the truth is that in 1902,"},{"time":137253,"text":"bears weren't cute and cuddly."},{"time":138881,"text":"I mean, they looked the same,"},{"time":140182,"text":"but no one thought of them that way."},{"time":141315,"text":"In 1902, bears were monsters."},{"time":144161,"text":"Bears were something that frickin' terrified kids."},{"time":147485,"text":"For generations at that point,"},{"time":149145,"text":"the bear had been a shorthand for all the danger"},{"time":152418,"text":"that people were encountering on the frontier,"},{"time":154177,"text":"and the federal government was actually"},{"time":155545,"text":"systematically exterminating bears"},{"time":157830,"text":"and lots of other predators too,"},{"time":159083,"text":"like coyotes and wolves."},{"time":160933,"text":"These animals, they were being demonized."},{"time":162781,"text":"They were called murderers"},{"time":164079,"text":"because they killed people's livestock."},{"time":166235,"text":"One government biologist, he explained this"},{"time":168773,"text":"war on animals like the bear by saying"},{"time":170953,"text":"that they no longer had a place"},{"time":173343,"text":"in our advancing civilization,"},{"time":175589,"text":"and so we were just clearing them out of the way."},{"time":179317,"text":"In one 10-year period, close to half a million wolves"},{"time":183083,"text":"had been slaughtered."},{"time":184290,"text":"The grizzly would soon be wiped out"},{"time":186147,"text":"from 95 percent of its original territory,"},{"time":189580,"text":"and whereas once there had been 30 million bison"},{"time":192802,"text":"moving across the plains, and you would have"},{"time":194420,"text":"these stories of trains having to stop"},{"time":196128,"text":"for four or five hours so that these thick,"},{"time":198116,"text":"living rivers of the animals could pour over the tracks,"},{"time":201444,"text":"now, by 1902, there were maybe \nless than 100 left in the wild."},{"time":206803,"text":"And so what I'm saying is, the teddy bear was born"},{"time":209840,"text":"into the middle of this great spasm of extermination,"},{"time":213364,"text":"and you can see it as a sign that"},{"time":214910,"text":"maybe some people deep down"},{"time":216550,"text":"were starting to feel conflicted about all that killing."},{"time":220616,"text":"America still hated the bear and feared it,"},{"time":223644,"text":"but all of a sudden, America also wanted"},{"time":225200,"text":"to give the bear a great big hug."}]},{"cues":[{"time":228086,"text":"So this is something that I've been really\ncurious about in the last few years."},{"time":230315,"text":"How do we imagine animals,"},{"time":231989,"text":"how do we think and feel about them,"},{"time":233587,"text":"and how do their reputations get written"},{"time":236063,"text":"and then rewritten in our minds?"},{"time":238319,"text":"We're here living in the eye of a great storm"},{"time":241163,"text":"of extinction where half the species on the planet"},{"time":244015,"text":"could be gone by the end of the century,"},{"time":246167,"text":"and so why is it that we come to care about"},{"time":247701,"text":"some of those species and not others?"},{"time":250571,"text":"Well, there's a new field, a relatively new field"},{"time":252701,"text":"of social science that started looking at"},{"time":254147,"text":"these questions and trying to unpack the powerful"},{"time":256315,"text":"and sometimes pretty schizophrenic relationships"},{"time":258047,"text":"that we have to animals,"},{"time":260168,"text":"and I spent a lot of time looking through"},{"time":261609,"text":"their academic journals,"},{"time":263633,"text":"and all I can really say is that their findings"},{"time":265439,"text":"are astonishingly wide-ranging."},{"time":267425,"text":"So some of my favorites include that"},{"time":269251,"text":"the more television a person\nwatches in Upstate New York,"},{"time":271892,"text":"the more he or she is afraid"},{"time":273545,"text":"of being attacked by a black bear."},{"time":275242,"text":"If you show a tiger to an American,"},{"time":278030,"text":"they're much more likely to assume that it's female"},{"time":280140,"text":"and not male."},{"time":281400,"text":"In a study where a fake snake"},{"time":283168,"text":"and a fake turtle were put on the side of the road,"},{"time":285153,"text":"drivers hit the snake much\nmore often than the turtle,"},{"time":287405,"text":"and about three percent of\ndrivers who hit the fake animals"},{"time":289469,"text":"seemed to do it on purpose."},{"time":291747,"text":"Women are more likely than men to get a"},{"time":294337,"text":"\"magical feeling\" when they see dolphins in the surf."},{"time":297372,"text":"Sixty-eight percent of mothers with"},{"time":299184,"text":"\"high feelings of entitlement and self-esteem\""},{"time":302564,"text":"identified with the dancing cats"},{"time":304209,"text":"in a commercial for Purina. (Laughter)"},{"time":306674,"text":"Americans consider lobsters"},{"time":308359,"text":"more important than pigeons"},{"time":309655,"text":"but also much, much stupider."},{"time":311841,"text":"Wild turkeys are seen as only slightly\nmore dangerous than sea otters,"},{"time":314837,"text":"and pandas are twice as lovable as ladybugs."}]},{"cues":[{"time":320010,"text":"So some of this is physical, right?"},{"time":321443,"text":"We tend to sympathize more\nwith animals that look like us,"},{"time":324066,"text":"and especially that resemble human babies,"},{"time":325696,"text":"so with big, forward-facing eyes"},{"time":327123,"text":"and circular faces,"},{"time":328385,"text":"kind of a roly-poly posture."},{"time":330119,"text":"This is why, if you get a Christmas card from, like,"},{"time":332154,"text":"your great aunt in Minnesota,"},{"time":333294,"text":"there's usually a fuzzy penguin chick on it,"},{"time":334867,"text":"and not something like a Glacier Bay wolf spider."},{"time":337579,"text":"But it's not all physical, right?"},{"time":340248,"text":"There's a cultural dimension to\nhow we think about animals,"},{"time":343432,"text":"and we're telling stories about these animals,"},{"time":345312,"text":"and like all stories,"},{"time":346670,"text":"they are shaped by the times and the places"},{"time":348743,"text":"in which we're telling them."},{"time":349619,"text":"So think about that moment"},{"time":351093,"text":"back in 1902 again where a ferocious bear"},{"time":354011,"text":"became a teddy bear."},{"time":355444,"text":"What was the context?\nWell, America was urbanizing."},{"time":358511,"text":"For the first time, nearly a\nmajority of people lived in cities,"},{"time":361270,"text":"so there was a growing distance\nbetween us and nature."},{"time":363706,"text":"There was a safe space where we could"},{"time":365498,"text":"reconsider the bear and romanticize it."},{"time":368172,"text":"Nature could only start to\nseem this pure and adorable"},{"time":370906,"text":"because we didn't have to be afraid of it anymore."},{"time":373660,"text":"And you can see that cycle playing out"},{"time":375185,"text":"again and again with all kinds of animals."},{"time":377347,"text":"It seems like we're always stuck between"},{"time":379223,"text":"demonizing a species and wanting to wipe it out,"},{"time":381630,"text":"and then when we get very close to doing that,"},{"time":383210,"text":"empathizing with it as an underdog"},{"time":385747,"text":"and wanting to show it compassion."},{"time":388272,"text":"So we exert our power,"},{"time":390070,"text":"but then we're unsettled"},{"time":391514,"text":"by how powerful we are."}]},{"cues":[{"time":394289,"text":"So for example, this is one of"},{"time":396413,"text":"probably thousands of letters and drawings"},{"time":399050,"text":"that kids sent to the Bush administration,"},{"time":400594,"text":"begging it to protect the polar bear"},{"time":402305,"text":"under the Endangered Species Act,"},{"time":403572,"text":"and these were sent back in the mid-2000s,"},{"time":406080,"text":"when awareness of climate\nchange was suddenly surging."},{"time":408233,"text":"We kept seeing that image of a polar bear"},{"time":409562,"text":"stranded on a little ice floe"},{"time":410980,"text":"looking really morose."},{"time":412327,"text":"I spent days looking through these files."},{"time":414091,"text":"I really love them. This one's my favorite."},{"time":416250,"text":"If you can see, it's a polar bear that's drowning"},{"time":418361,"text":"and then it's also being eaten simultaneously"},{"time":420776,"text":"by a lobster and a shark."},{"time":423480,"text":"This one came from a kid named Fritz,"},{"time":425192,"text":"and he's actually got a solution to climate change."},{"time":426886,"text":"He's got it all worked out to an ethanol-based solution."},{"time":428732,"text":"He says, \"I feel bad about the polar bears."},{"time":431382,"text":"I like polar bears."},{"time":433494,"text":"Everyone can use corn juice for cars. From Fritz.\""},{"time":439280,"text":"So 200 years ago, you would have Arctic explorers"},{"time":442275,"text":"writing about polar bears leaping into their boats"},{"time":444583,"text":"and trying to devour them,"},{"time":445826,"text":"even if they lit the bear on fire,"},{"time":447493,"text":"but these kids don't see the polar bear that way,"},{"time":449673,"text":"and actually they don't even see the polar bear"},{"time":451463,"text":"the way that I did back in the '80s."},{"time":453223,"text":"I mean, we thought of these animals"},{"time":454343,"text":"as mysterious and terrifying lords of the Arctic."},{"time":457209,"text":"But look now how quickly that climate change"},{"time":459529,"text":"has flipped the image of the animal in our minds."},{"time":462415,"text":"It's gone from that bloodthirsty man-killer"},{"time":464855,"text":"to this delicate, drowning victim,"},{"time":467929,"text":"and when you think about it, that's kind of"},{"time":469442,"text":"the conclusion to the story"},{"time":471423,"text":"that the teddy bear started telling back in 1902,"},{"time":474725,"text":"because back then, America had more or less"},{"time":477615,"text":"conquered its share of the continent."},{"time":478930,"text":"We were just getting around to"},{"time":480233,"text":"polishing off these last wild predators."},{"time":482251,"text":"Now, society's reach has expanded"},{"time":484805,"text":"all the way to the top of the world,"},{"time":486865,"text":"and it's made even these, the most remote,"},{"time":489159,"text":"the most powerful bears on the planet,"},{"time":491191,"text":"seem like adorable and blameless victims."}]},{"cues":[{"time":494690,"text":"But you know, there's also a\npostscript to the teddy bear story"},{"time":497581,"text":"that not a lot of people talk about."},{"time":499218,"text":"We're going to talk about it,"},{"time":501001,"text":"because even though it didn't really take long"},{"time":503174,"text":"after Roosevelt's hunt in 1902"},{"time":504974,"text":"for the toy to become a full-blown craze,"},{"time":506951,"text":"most people figured it was a fad,"},{"time":509452,"text":"it was a sort of silly political novelty item"},{"time":511684,"text":"and it would go away once the president left office,"},{"time":513926,"text":"and so by 1909, when Roosevelt's successor,"},{"time":517723,"text":"William Howard Taft,"},{"time":519148,"text":"was getting ready to be inaugurated,"},{"time":520556,"text":"the toy industry was on the hunt"},{"time":522488,"text":"for the next big thing."},{"time":525315,"text":"They didn't do too well."}]},{"cues":[{"time":527572,"text":"That January, Taft was the guest of honor"},{"time":530171,"text":"at a banquet in Atlanta,"},{"time":531610,"text":"and for days in advance,"},{"time":533479,"text":"the big news was the menu."},{"time":534924,"text":"They were going to be serving him"},{"time":536010,"text":"a Southern specialty, a delicacy, really,"},{"time":538074,"text":"called possum and taters."},{"time":540980,"text":"So you would have a whole opossum"},{"time":543582,"text":"roasted on a bed of sweet potatoes,"},{"time":544947,"text":"and then sometimes they'd leave"},{"time":546394,"text":"the big tail on it like a big, meaty noodle."},{"time":549878,"text":"The one brought to Taft's table"},{"time":551557,"text":"weighed 18 pounds."},{"time":554742,"text":"So after dinner, the orchestra started to play,"},{"time":557446,"text":"and the guests burst into song,"},{"time":559286,"text":"and all of a sudden, Taft was surprised"},{"time":560910,"text":"with the presentation of a gift"},{"time":562632,"text":"from a group of local supporters,"},{"time":564524,"text":"and this was a stuffed opossum toy,"},{"time":566960,"text":"all beady-eyed and bald-eared,"},{"time":569170,"text":"and it was a new product they were putting forward"},{"time":571870,"text":"to be the William Taft presidency's answer"},{"time":574592,"text":"to Teddy Roosevelt's teddy bear."},{"time":578140,"text":"They were calling it the \"billy possum.\""},{"time":582586,"text":"Within 24 hours, the Georgia Billy Possum Company"},{"time":586436,"text":"was up and running, brokering deals"},{"time":587986,"text":"for these things nationwide,"},{"time":589586,"text":"and the Los Angeles Times announced,"},{"time":591184,"text":"very confidently, \"The teddy bear"},{"time":593136,"text":"has been relegated to a seat in the rear,"},{"time":595662,"text":"and for four years, possibly eight,"},{"time":598260,"text":"the children of the United States"},{"time":600214,"text":"will play with billy possum.\""},{"time":603446,"text":"So from that point, there was a fit of opossum fever."},{"time":605570,"text":"There were billy possum postcards, billy possum pins,"},{"time":608038,"text":"billy possum pitchers for your cream at coffee time."},{"time":610200,"text":"There were smaller billy possums on a stick"},{"time":611930,"text":"that kids could wave around like flags."},{"time":614872,"text":"But even with all this marketing,"},{"time":616790,"text":"the life of the billy possum"},{"time":618820,"text":"turned out to be just pathetically brief."},{"time":622004,"text":"The toy was an absolute flop,"},{"time":624047,"text":"and it was almost completely forgotten"},{"time":625626,"text":"by the end of the year,"},{"time":626994,"text":"and what that means is that the billy possum"},{"time":629086,"text":"didn't even make it to Christmastime,"},{"time":630586,"text":"which when you think about it is"},{"time":631626,"text":"a special sort of tragedy for a toy."}]},{"cues":[{"time":635475,"text":"So we can explain that failure two ways."},{"time":637398,"text":"The first, well, it's pretty obvious."},{"time":639588,"text":"I'm going to go ahead and say it out loud anyway:"},{"time":641476,"text":"Opossums are hideous. (Laughter)"},{"time":644337,"text":"But maybe more importantly is that"},{"time":647000,"text":"the story of the billy possum was all wrong,"},{"time":649690,"text":"especially compared"},{"time":651221,"text":"to the backstory of the teddy bear."},{"time":653302,"text":"Think about it: for most of\nhuman's evolutionary history,"},{"time":655544,"text":"what's made bears impressive to us"},{"time":657869,"text":"has been their complete independence from us."},{"time":660041,"text":"It's that they live these parallel lives"},{"time":662626,"text":"as menaces and competitors."},{"time":665131,"text":"By the time Roosevelt went hunting in Mississippi,"},{"time":667486,"text":"that stature was being crushed,"},{"time":669464,"text":"and the animal that he had roped to a tree"},{"time":671702,"text":"really was a symbol for all bears."},{"time":674003,"text":"Whether those animals lived or died now"},{"time":676430,"text":"was entirely up to the compassion"},{"time":679440,"text":"or the indifference of people."},{"time":681857,"text":"That said something really ominous"},{"time":683681,"text":"about the future of bears,"},{"time":686363,"text":"but it also said something very \nunsettling about who we'd become,"},{"time":689500,"text":"if the survival of even an animal like that"},{"time":691942,"text":"was up to us now."},{"time":694231,"text":"So now, a century later, if you're at all"},{"time":696311,"text":"paying attention to what's\nhappening in the environment,"},{"time":698511,"text":"you feel that discomfort so much more intensely."},{"time":702189,"text":"We're living now in an age of what scientists"},{"time":705011,"text":"have started to call \"conservation reliance,\""},{"time":707221,"text":"and what that term means is that we've disrupted"},{"time":709411,"text":"so much that nature can't possibly\nstand on its own anymore,"},{"time":712575,"text":"and most endangered species"},{"time":714277,"text":"are only going to survive"},{"time":716049,"text":"if we stay out there in the landscape"},{"time":718167,"text":"riggging the world around them in their favor."},{"time":720663,"text":"So we've gone hands-on"},{"time":722519,"text":"and we can't ever take our hands off,"},{"time":724957,"text":"and that's a hell of a lot of work."},{"time":726850,"text":"Right now, we're training condors"},{"time":729929,"text":"not to perch on power lines."},{"time":731881,"text":"We teach whooping cranes\nto migrate south for the winter"},{"time":734594,"text":"behind little ultra-light airplanes."},{"time":736893,"text":"We're out there feeding plague vaccine to ferrets."},{"time":740202,"text":"We monitor pygmy rabbits with drones."},{"time":744552,"text":"So we've gone from annihilating species"},{"time":747869,"text":"to micromanaging the survival of a lot of species"},{"time":751373,"text":"indefinitely, and which ones?"},{"time":753315,"text":"Well, the ones that we've told"},{"time":754507,"text":"compelling stories about,"},{"time":756131,"text":"the ones we've decided ought to stick around."},{"time":759346,"text":"The line between conservation and domestication"},{"time":762920,"text":"is blurred."}]},{"cues":[{"time":764945,"text":"So what I've been saying is that the stories"},{"time":766797,"text":"that we tell about wild animals are so subjective"},{"time":769420,"text":"they can be irrational"},{"time":770582,"text":"or romanticized or sensationalized."},{"time":772766,"text":"Sometimes they just have\nnothing to do with the facts."},{"time":775515,"text":"But in a world of conservation reliance,"},{"time":778765,"text":"those stories have very real consequences,"},{"time":780971,"text":"because now, how we feel about an animal"},{"time":783399,"text":"affects its survival"},{"time":785029,"text":"more than anything that you read about"},{"time":787389,"text":"in ecology textbooks."},{"time":789438,"text":"Storytelling matters now."},{"time":791840,"text":"Emotion matters."},{"time":793373,"text":"Our imagination has become an ecological force."},{"time":799025,"text":"And so maybe the teddy bear worked in part"},{"time":800962,"text":"because the legend of Roosevelt"},{"time":803653,"text":"and that bear in Mississippi"},{"time":805708,"text":"was kind of like an allegory"},{"time":807168,"text":"of this great responsibility that society"},{"time":809261,"text":"was just beginning to face up to back then."},{"time":811955,"text":"It would be another 71 years"},{"time":814375,"text":"before the Endangered Species Act was passed,"},{"time":816229,"text":"but really, here's its whole ethos"},{"time":818559,"text":"boiled down into something like a scene"},{"time":820513,"text":"you'd see in a stained glass window."},{"time":822859,"text":"The bear is a helpless victim tied to a tree,"},{"time":825851,"text":"and the president of the United States"},{"time":828402,"text":"decided to show it some mercy."},{"time":830794,"text":"Thank you."},{"time":833440,"text":"(Applause)"},{"time":835154,"text":"[Illustrations by Wendy MacNaughton]"}]}]}